public static class DialogueFootprints{
 	public static List<Dialogue> Dialogues= new List<Dialogue>(); 
	public static void Init(){
		Dialogues.Add(new Dialogue(@"Look at you. Lean. Hungry. I like hungry. Hungry keeps a man sharp. Me? I’m ravenous, kid. And right now, the Marcone family has a serious pest problem blocking our supply lines down at the pier.
The Vipers. They think they can just sit on our turf? Scoop the cream right off our top? No. Nonono. You don’t nibble on Meatball’s plate and live to tell the tale.
Here’s the play. I don’t want you to just clear the pier. I want an all-you-can-eat buffet of chaos. Every single jacket wearing yellow down there? Extinct. You don't stop when they start running. You don't stop when they start begging. You keep feeding that lead until the barrel melts.
Think of it like an appetizer. The more Vipers you put in the dirt tonight, the bigger your slice of the pie tomorrow. I want a headcount that makes the coroner’s stomach turn. Leave 'em stacked like cordwood, kid.
They’re at the shipping yard right now, probably feeling real safe. Go ruin their appetite. Permanently. If the cops show up? Well, they can get a taste of it too. Don't leave a single crumb.
What are you still standing here for? Go get fat on 'em.", Resources.Heads._chillguy, Resources.Dialogues.D1)); 
	}
}
